    "causal_summary": "A 10-angle read-only deep-research study on improving the quality and safety of the spec-kit generated JSON metadata, description.json and graph-metadata.json, and the generators that produce them. Ten gpt-5.5-fast xhigh angle seats reading the live generator, parser, schema, discovery, and validator code converged on a diagnosis: two safety classes dominate, broad-walk over-reach and non-idempotent writes, both surfacing as unscoped cross-session commit churn, plus a latent lineage-loss risk on the merge path. The root-cause fixes are convergent, a single shared spec-folder identity resolver four angles reached and a first-class generated-metadata validator in strict mode three angles reached. A claude skeptical pass confirmed two P0 root causes with file:line, the status normalizer admits em-dash prose and mergeGraphMetadata drops parent_id and children_ids, and downgraded four over-claims, z_future already fixed, z_archive divergence by-design, graph metadata already idempotent, and triple-counted drift merged. The study produced 14 ranked proposals across four safety classes with a recommended build order.",
